  "prompt": "What is my Asian size if I'm XS in the U.S.?",
  "response": "Asian sizing can differ significantly from U.S. sizing, so it's important to check specific sizing charts for the brand or retailer you are interested in. However, a general guideline for converting U.S. sizes to Asian sizes is as follows:\n\n- If you wear an XS in U.S. sizes, you might typically wear a size S or M in Asian sizes, depending on the cut and fit of the clothing. \n\nHere is a rough conversion:\n\n- U.S. XS \u2192 Asian S or M\n\nIt's always best to consult the specific brand's sizing chart for the most accurate fit, as sizes can vary between manufacturers.",
